metadata.name: CrossWorlds #99
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #2411
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: color combinations #95
metadata.description:
the 'color combinations' series was developed as an exercise of combining colors from a single defined palette and the attempt to make all 15 selected colors being able to work within each other.

the constant pursuit for perfectionism made me design more than 200 tentatives of creating a perfect circle, and therefore the circle is the rarest output for the series.

i hope this series serves as a reference and inspire everyone out there.

2,340 possible combinations.
the closer the shape to the circle the rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%.
the bigger the shape the rarer - ranging from 30% to 20%.
beige and black colors are rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%

metadata.name: Tess #14
metadata.description:
Tessellation is the process of creating a two-dimensional or three-dimensional object from a set of smaller pieces that fit together without any gaps or overlaps. Glitch art is a type of art that is created by deliberately introducing errors or faults into digital images or videos.

Some artists combine these two concepts to create unsettling tessellation glitches. By creating tessellations out of digital images that contain glitches, they are able to create images that are both visually interesting and subtly disturbing.

metadata.name: Across Paper Stones #97
metadata.description:
Wherever you want to go, you'll find a path to take you there.

Each tile is made up of two deformed rectangles. One is drawn with a drifting, fragmented outline.

Over thirty color palettes are shuffled together on each output, helping form slight edges between groups.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Floating Point  #99
metadata.description:
'Floating Point' by pixelwank 

Inspired by pastel smudging and the aerial photography of Rich Caldwell, Floating Point has impressions of a landscape and other structures. 

Homage to floating point numbers and how just one decimal difference can change it all. 

Floating Point is also the fictional name of the place where this work takes me, where does it take you?

In live mode, click the image or press 's' or 'S' to save 3000x4000 png 

Thanks for collecting 
Shoutout Circolors for the support & frenship <3 

Made with p5js 
© pixelwank - CC BY 3.0, August 2022

metadata.name: Updraft #202
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: White Night Vol.1 #44
metadata.description:
I have a long-term photography project called “White Night”, which explores special images of trees through black and white inversion.

I attempt to generate similar images by code, and this is the start of the journey.

Made with p5js.

Controls:
- Press “f” to toggle the frame, there is my signature on the mat inside the frame.
- Press “s” to save the image displayed at that moment as a PNG file.
- Change the canvas size by adding “size” URL parameter, for example: &size=1000 (you may add this and lower the number if your device can’t render properly)

objkt.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #3

metadata.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #3
metadata.description:
This is a building generation made by pure code.

Urbanization at the almost everywhere in the world has stepped into an accelerating phase in last century. Buildings bring magnificent achievements and represent the human power over nature. But, following these tall and crowd buildings one by one, where are we going?

In this work, I generate different types of building with a special viewpoint, which represent different concepts of states we are going to. Hope you enjoy these varieties and coincidences.

Variables:
- 4 modes
- 4 environments
- 3 orbs
- 3 building density
- 3 building structures

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Woolly #149
metadata.description:
Combining both CPU and GPU techniques to render a raymarched scene using a grid of lines according to the surface data from the shader output. 

* Variations:
- Number of balls
- Waves pattern
- Perspective
- Colors
- 10% chance of inverted version

CPU and GPU intensive
